  abstract = {In modelling pellet strength, researchers have presented analyses for the three regimes of pellet strength (the pendular, funicular and capillary regimes) without defining quantitatively the boundaries of the regimes. The problem reduces to a determination of the upper limit of moisture content of a pellet in the pendular state. For a pellet comprised of randomly packed, equal-sized spherical particles, this upper limit of moisture content is computed at 13.6 vol.% corresponding to a saturation of 34.1 vol.%. {\textcopyright} 1991.},
